    <!-- Introduction Section -->
    <section id="intro">
        <h2>Welcome to the Guided Workflow: Pitching VAS Products</h2>
        <p>This interactive guide will take you through the key steps involved in effectively pitching VAS (Value-Added Services) products to customers. Each step will help you understand how to engage the customer, present the right products, and address any questions they may have. Let’s get started!</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 1: Probing Questions -->
    <section id="step1">
        <h2>Step 1: Probing Questions (Creating the Need)</h2>
        <p>Start by asking probing questions to understand the customer's needs and identify gaps where VAS products could help. Below are some sample questions:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>For Wi-Fi Coverage:</strong> "Hi [Customer’s Name], how's the Wi-Fi coverage in your house? Do you experience any dead spots or lag when streaming?"</li>
            <li><strong>For Security Protection:</strong> "Hi [Customer’s Name], do you have any protection on your computer or smart devices from digital threats like malware or hacking?"</li>
            <li><strong>For Affordable TV Alternatives:</strong> "Hi [Customer’s Name], are you looking for a more affordable alternative to your current cable TV service?"</li>
        </ul>
        <button onclick="showQuiz('step1-quiz')">Test Your Knowledge: Probing Questions</button>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 1 Quiz -->
    <section id="step1-quiz" style="display:none;">
        <h3>Probing Questions Quiz</h3>
        <p>Choose the most appropriate question to ask a customer interested in improving Wi-Fi coverage:</p>
        <form id="quiz-form-step1">
            <label for="question1">1. How often do you stream content on your TV?</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q1a1" name="q1" value="wrong"> Option 1: "How often do you stream content on your TV?"<br>
            <input type="radio" id="q1a2" name="q1" value="correct"> Option 2: "Do you experience any dead spots or lag when streaming?"<br>
            <br>
            <input type="submit" value="Submit Quiz">
        </form>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 2: Pitch the Pitch -->
    <section id="step2">
        <h2>Step 2: Pitch the Pitch</h2>
        <p>Once you've identified the customer’s needs, it’s time to pitch the right VAS product:</p>
        <p>"Hi [Customer’s Name], based on what you've shared, I’d like to let you know that we offer a range of excellent products that can help improve your experience:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Wi-Fi Coverage:</strong> Whole Home Wi-Fi (eliminate dead spots and extend your signal).</li>
            <li><strong>Security Protection:</strong> Frontier Secure, Eero Secure, Total Shield, and My Premium Tech Pro.</li>
            <li><strong>Affordable TV Alternatives:</strong> YouTube TV or Netflix subscriptions.</li>
        </ul>
        <button onclick="showQuiz('step2-quiz')">Test Your Knowledge: The Pitch</button>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 2 Quiz -->
    <section id="step2-quiz" style="display:none;">
        <h3>Pitch the Pitch Quiz</h3>
        <p>Which of the following would be a good product to pitch if a customer mentions they want better Wi-Fi coverage?</p>
        <form id="quiz-form-step2">
            <label for="question2">1. Whole Home Wi-Fi</label><br>
            <input type="radio" id="q2a1" name="q2" value="correct"> Option 1: "Whole Home Wi-Fi"<br>
